ciscoEsIpAddr.name: ciscoEsIpAddr
ciscoEsIpAddr.description: The IP address of the current vlan.

ciscoEsNetMask.name: ciscoEsNetMask
ciscoEsNetMask.description: The subnet mask of the current vlan.

ciscoEsDefaultGateway.name: ciscoEsDefaultGateway
ciscoEsDefaultGateway.description: IP default gateway of the current vlan.

ciscoEsSysCurTime.name: ciscoEsSysCurTime
ciscoEsSysCurTime.description: Current time at the switch. To set the time use the format yyyy mm dd hh mm ss. All fields are required. Setting this object will reset the time in all the switches in the stack to the new value.

ciscoEsConfiguration.name: ciscoEsConfiguration
ciscoEsConfiguration.description: The stack configuration of the system. A system can exist in three possible configurations. 1. Stand alone mode where the system has only one switch and is not connected to any other switches. 2. Back to Back mode in which a pair of switches are connected back to back through Stack Port. 3. Matrix mode in which the stack has up to eight switches connected to a Matrix through the Stack Port.

ciscoEsNumSwitches.name: ciscoEsNumSwitches
ciscoEsNumSwitches.description: Total number of switches in the stack.

ciscoEsStackStatus.name: ciscoEsStackStatus
ciscoEsStackStatus.description: Stack status indicates if the stack is going through the Stack Management Update protocol. Management stations should check this status if they receive a generr on a SET request for any of the stack wide attributes.

ciscoEsTftpServerDomain.name: ciscoEsTftpServerDomain
ciscoEsTftpServerDomain.description: VLAN to which the server is connected.

ciscoEsTftpFileLoc.name: ciscoEsTftpFileLoc
ciscoEsTftpFileLoc.description: Location of the binary file on the server.

ciscoEsSetLock.name: ciscoEsSetLock
ciscoEsSetLock.description: This object has not been in use since 2.0 release and there are currently no plans to implement it as defined below. This object when set to the manager's IP address locks out every other manager from doing any SET operations. This lock out expires after a fixed interval of 5 minutes. The Manager holding the lock can renew the lock by doing SET on this object again before the timeout expires otherwise it will contend with other managers trying to lock. The IP Address value should match the IP address that the manager uses to generate the SET request.

ciscoEsProStackMatrixStatus.name: ciscoEsProStackMatrixStatus
ciscoEsProStackMatrixStatus.description: Active Matrix module in the stack. This object is set to none if the switch is not connected to a Matrix.

ciscoEsNumMatrixModules.name: ciscoEsNumMatrixModules
ciscoEsNumMatrixModules.description: Number of Matrix modules in the stack. This object is set to zero if the switch is not connected to a Matrix.

ciscoEsLLPortDsbld.name: ciscoEsLLPortDsbld
ciscoEsLLPortDsbld.description: This OID is sent out along with the LINK_DOWN Trap only when the port is disabled due to the port security feature (learn and lock). Port could be disabled due to the discovery of invalid MAC address.

ciscoEsTrapRcvrTable.name: ciscoEsTrapRcvrTable
ciscoEsTrapRcvrTable.description: Trap Receiver Table for each vlan.

ciscoEsTrapRcvrEntry.name: ciscoEsTrapRcvrEntry
ciscoEsTrapRcvrEntry.description: Definition of each row in the vlan specific trap receiver table.

ciscoEsTrapRcvrIndex.name: ciscoEsTrapRcvrIndex
ciscoEsTrapRcvrIndex.description: Trap receiver index for each entry.

ciscoEsTrapRcvrStatus.name: ciscoEsTrapRcvrStatus
ciscoEsTrapRcvrStatus.description: Setting the value of this object to invalid(3) deletes the row from the table. The value invalid(3) should never be returned on a GET. Setting this value to create(4) causes a new row to be created if the row does not already exist. To create a new row set ciscoEsTrapRcvrStatus to create(4) and ciscoEsTrapRcvrIndex to any valid index which does not already exist. The value returned on GETs should be valid(2) or other(1), which is used to indicate any other condition.

ciscoEsTrapRcvrIpAddress.name: ciscoEsTrapRcvrIpAddress
ciscoEsTrapRcvrIpAddress.description: IP address for an SNMP manager that is to receive the trap.

ciscoEsTrapRcvrVLANs.name: ciscoEsTrapRcvrVLANs
ciscoEsTrapRcvrVLANs.description: VLANs to which traps to this target are sent out on. Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight vlans, with the first octet specifying vlans 0 through 7, the second octet specifying vlans 8 through 15, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered vlan, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered vlan. Thus, each vlan of the stack is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that vlan is included in the set of ports; the vlan is not included if its bit has a value of '0'.

ciscoEsStackTable.name: ciscoEsStackTable
ciscoEsStackTable.description: Stack information table. This table provides the current configuration of the stack. It also provides a mapping of Switch Numbers to their addresses. The Management Application is required to retrieve this table and verify its own view of the stack periodically and/or when it receives a trap indicating a change in the stack configuration.

ciscoEsStackEntry.name: ciscoEsStackEntry
ciscoEsStackEntry.description: Definition of each row in the Stack Table

ciscoEsStackSwitchNumber.name: ciscoEsStackSwitchNumber
ciscoEsStackSwitchNumber.description: Switch number determined by the port number that the switch is connected to in a Matrix or as determined by the Stack Management software when two switches are connected back to back.

ciscoEsStackSwitchFwVersion.name: ciscoEsStackSwitchFwVersion
ciscoEsStackSwitchFwVersion.description: Version number for the firmware running on the switch.

ciscoEsStackSwitchHwVersion.name: ciscoEsStackSwitchHwVersion
ciscoEsStackSwitchHwVersion.description: Hardware version number for the switch.

ciscoEsStackSwitchUptime.name: ciscoEsStackSwitchUptime
ciscoEsStackSwitchUptime.description: Time ticks since the switch was last reset.

ciscoEsStackSwitchStatus.name: ciscoEsStackSwitchStatus
ciscoEsStackSwitchStatus.description: Operational status of the box. Setting this value to either coldReset (2) or warmReset (3) will cause cold start or warm start to occur after a specific time delay.

ciscoEsStackSwitchMemory.name: ciscoEsStackSwitchMemory
ciscoEsStackSwitchMemory.description: Installed memory on the switch in MB.

ciscoEsStackSwitchProbe.name: ciscoEsStackSwitchProbe
ciscoEsStackSwitchProbe.description: Port number to be monitored through the SwitchProbe. Setting this object to zero turns off SwitchProbe.

ciscoEsStackSwitchProbeDirection.name: ciscoEsStackSwitchProbeDirection
ciscoEsStackSwitchProbeDirection.description: Direction of traffic to monitor on the SwitchProbe.

ciscoEsStackSwitchFeatureStatus.name: ciscoEsStackSwitchFeatureStatus
ciscoEsStackSwitchFeatureStatus.description: This object indicates whether the switch is enabled to support enhanced features.

ciscoEsStackSwitchFeatureKey.name: ciscoEsStackSwitchFeatureKey
ciscoEsStackSwitchFeatureKey.description: Feature key to enable enhanced features.

ciscoEsStackSwitchPorts.name: ciscoEsStackSwitchPorts
ciscoEsStackSwitchPorts.description: A bit mask representing all the ports present in this switch. Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the EtherSwitch is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'.

ciscoEsStackSwitchAgingTime.name: ciscoEsStackSwitchAgingTime
ciscoEsStackSwitchAgingTime.description: Aging time in minutes for the master address table entries on this switch.

ciscoEsStackSwitchAgingLevel.name: ciscoEsStackSwitchAgingLevel
ciscoEsStackSwitchAgingLevel.description: Threshold to demand age the master address table. All numbers refer to percentage of the address table. The only values accepted by the agent are 50,60,70,80,90 and 0. Setting the value to 0 disables demand aging.

ciscoEsStackSwitchBufferOverruns.name: ciscoEsStackSwitchBufferOverruns
ciscoEsStackSwitchBufferOverruns.description: Number of times the switch was out of buffers.

ciscoEsStackSwitchSoftwareFrames.name: ciscoEsStackSwitchSoftwareFrames
ciscoEsStackSwitchSoftwareFrames.description: Total number of frames sent to the CPU on this switch.

ciscoEsStackSwitchInErrFrames.name: ciscoEsStackSwitchInErrFrames
ciscoEsStackSwitchInErrFrames.description: Total number of frames in error on this switch.

ciscoEsStackSwitchInShortFrames.name: ciscoEsStackSwitchInShortFrames
ciscoEsStackSwitchInShortFrames.description: Total number of frames which were too short received on this switch.

ciscoEsStackSwitchInLongFrames.name: ciscoEsStackSwitchInLongFrames
ciscoEsStackSwitchInLongFrames.description: Total number of frames which were too long received on this switch.

ciscoEsStackSwitchOutDroppedFrames.name: ciscoEsStackSwitchOutDroppedFrames
ciscoEsStackSwitchOutDroppedFrames.description: Total number of received frames dropped by switch.

ciscoEsStackSwitchInNoSpaceFrames.name: ciscoEsStackSwitchInNoSpaceFrames
ciscoEsStackSwitchInNoSpaceFrames.description: Number of times incoming frames had to be dropped because of no more memory available.

ciscoEsStackSwitchOutTotalReqs.name: ciscoEsStackSwitchOutTotalReqs
ciscoEsStackSwitchOutTotalReqs.description: Total number of requests made by the CPU to send out a frame.

ciscoEsStackSwitchOutTotalFrames.name: ciscoEsStackSwitchOutTotalFrames
ciscoEsStackSwitchOutTotalFrames.description: Total number of frames sent out from this switch requested by the CPU.

ciscoEsStackSwitchLongestHashChain.name: ciscoEsStackSwitchLongestHashChain
ciscoEsStackSwitchLongestHashChain.description: The length of the longest hash chain in the CPU hash table.

ciscoEsStackSwitchHashTableFulls.name: ciscoEsStackSwitchHashTableFulls
ciscoEsStackSwitchHashTableFulls.description: Total number of times the hash table was full when trying to add an entry.

ciscoEsStackSwitchId.name: ciscoEsStackSwitchId
ciscoEsStackSwitchId.description: The switch Id used to uniquely identify the kind of the cisco ethernet switch.

ciscoEsStackSwitchDplxCtrl.name: ciscoEsStackSwitchDplxCtrl
ciscoEsStackSwitchDplxCtrl.description: Control of setting the ports to full or half duplex.

ciscoEsModTable.name: ciscoEsModTable
ciscoEsModTable.description: Module configuration table. Each EtherSwitch the set of 10 MB Ports is considered as slot 1. Each additional card which plugs into the system is numbered based on where the card is plugged into.

ciscoEsModEntry.name: ciscoEsModEntry
ciscoEsModEntry.description: Definition of each row in the Module Table

ciscoEsModSwitchNumber.name: ciscoEsModSwitchNumber
ciscoEsModSwitchNumber.description: Switch number determined by the port number that the switch is connected to in a Matrix or as determined by the Stack Management software when two switches are connected back to back.

ciscoEsModState.name: ciscoEsModState
ciscoEsModState.description: The state indicates the current operational state of the module.

ciscoEsModType.name: ciscoEsModType
ciscoEsModType.description: The type of module plugged in to the slot. Module type system (1) represents the mother board with the CPU and system memory. In RSM the system module always occupies slot 2. Module state none (6) represents a slot with no modules plugged in (indicated by ciscoEsModState).

ciscoEsModNumPorts.name: ciscoEsModNumPorts
ciscoEsModNumPorts.description: Total number of ports in the module.

ciscoEsModUptime.name: ciscoEsModUptime
ciscoEsModUptime.description: Time in 1/100 seconds since the module was last reset.

ciscoEsPortTable.name: ciscoEsPortTable
ciscoEsPortTable.description: A table of information about each port. For Cisco ports only the following Counters are valid: ciscoEsPortInFrames ciscoEsPortOutFrames ciscoEsPortInOctets ciscoEsPortOutOctets ciscoEsPortLongFrames ciscoEsPortShortFrames ciscoEsPortSWHandledFrames ciscoEsPortInBufOverflows ciscoEsPortOutBufOverflows ciscoEsPortPktsInErrors ciscoEsPortForwardedFrames All other Counters will return 0 for such ports.

ciscoEsPortEntry.name: ciscoEsPortEntry
ciscoEsPortEntry.description: Definition of rows in the port table.

ciscoEsPortSwitchNumber.name: ciscoEsPortSwitchNumber
ciscoEsPortSwitchNumber.description: Switch number determined by the port number that the switch is connected to in a Matrix or as determined by the Stack Management software when two switches are connected back to back.

ciscoEsPortNumber.name: ciscoEsPortNumber
ciscoEsPortNumber.description: A unique value for each port entry. The value corresponds the port number.

ciscoEsPortModNumber.name: ciscoEsPortModNumber
ciscoEsPortModNumber.description: Module number of the module that contains this port.

ciscoEsPortIfIndex.name: ciscoEsPortIfIndex
ciscoEsPortIfIndex.description: A pointer to the entry in the ifTable corresponding to this port.

ciscoEsPortDuplex.name: ciscoEsPortDuplex
ciscoEsPortDuplex.description: Indicates whether the port is jumper configured for full or half duplex operation. Note: internal connected ports are always halfDuplex(2).

ciscoEsPortRcvLocalFrames.name: ciscoEsPortRcvLocalFrames
ciscoEsPortRcvLocalFrames.description: Number of frames received where the destination is on this port.

ciscoEsPortForwardedFrames.name: ciscoEsPortForwardedFrames
ciscoEsPortForwardedFrames.description: Number of frames received on this port and forwarded to another port or the system module for processing.

ciscoEsPortMostStations.name: ciscoEsPortMostStations
ciscoEsPortMostStations.description: Highest number of stations ever active at any time since the last reset of the switch as seen by this port.

ciscoEsPortMaxStations.name: ciscoEsPortMaxStations
ciscoEsPortMaxStations.description: Maximum number of stations which the port can support simultaneously.

ciscoEsPortSWHandledFrames.name: ciscoEsPortSWHandledFrames
ciscoEsPortSWHandledFrames.description: Number of Frames received on this port and delivered to the system module for processing.

ciscoEsPortLocalStations.name: ciscoEsPortLocalStations
ciscoEsPortLocalStations.description: Number of stations on this port which belong to the local segment.

ciscoEsPortRemoteStations.name: ciscoEsPortRemoteStations
ciscoEsPortRemoteStations.description: Number of stations on this port which belong to another segment.

ciscoEsPortUnknownStaFrames.name: ciscoEsPortUnknownStaFrames
ciscoEsPortUnknownStaFrames.description: Number of unicast frames received on this port and forwarded to the system module for processing because the source or destination station address is not in the port's forwarding table.

ciscoEsPortResetStats.name: ciscoEsPortResetStats
ciscoEsPortResetStats.description: Setting this object to reset(3) causes all traffic counters for this port to be set to zero. Also the value of ciscoEsPortResetTimer is set to zero.

ciscoEsPortResetTimer.name: ciscoEsPortResetTimer
ciscoEsPortResetTimer.description: Time (in 100th second ticks) since the port counters were reset.

ciscoEsPortResetAddrs.name: ciscoEsPortResetAddrs
ciscoEsPortResetAddrs.description: Setting this object to reset(3) clears all address table entries for this port as well as setting all port traffic counters to zero and setting ciscoEsPortResetTimer to zero.

ciscoEsPortInFrames.name: ciscoEsPortInFrames
ciscoEsPortInFrames.description: Total Number of Frames received on this port.

ciscoEsPortOutFrames.name: ciscoEsPortOutFrames
ciscoEsPortOutFrames.description: Total Number of Frames transmitted by this port.

ciscoEsPortLongFrames.name: ciscoEsPortLongFrames
ciscoEsPortLongFrames.description: Total Number of Frames received on this port which were too long.

ciscoEsPortShortFrames.name: ciscoEsPortShortFrames
ciscoEsPortShortFrames.description: Total Number of Frames received on this port which were too short.

ciscoEsPortInBufOverflows.name: ciscoEsPortInBufOverflows
ciscoEsPortInBufOverflows.description: Total Number of Frames received on this port which caused a receive buffer overflow.

ciscoEsPortOutBufOverflows.name: ciscoEsPortOutBufOverflows
ciscoEsPortOutBufOverflows.description: Total Number of Frames which could not be transmitted from this port because of transmit buffer overflow.

ciscoEsPortRcvBcasts.name: ciscoEsPortRcvBcasts
ciscoEsPortRcvBcasts.description: Number of Broadcast Frames received on this port without errors.

ciscoEsPortRcvMcasts.name: ciscoEsPortRcvMcasts
ciscoEsPortRcvMcasts.description: Number of Multicast Frames received on this port without errors.

ciscoEsPortSwitchedFrames.name: ciscoEsPortSwitchedFrames
ciscoEsPortSwitchedFrames.description: Number of frames switched on this port.

ciscoEsPortInOctets.name: ciscoEsPortInOctets
ciscoEsPortInOctets.description: Total number of octets received through this port. This counter is the same as the ifInOctets counter in ifTable corresponding to this port.

ciscoEsPortOutOctets.name: ciscoEsPortOutOctets
ciscoEsPortOutOctets.description: Total number of octets transmitted from this port. This counter is the same as the ifOutOctets counter in ifTable corresponding to this port.

ciscoEsPortPktsInErrors.name: ciscoEsPortPktsInErrors
ciscoEsPortPktsInErrors.description: Total number of packets received or transmitted from this port and there was an error.

ciscoEsPortOprStatus.name: ciscoEsPortOprStatus
ciscoEsPortOprStatus.description: Operational status of the port. Failed is returned when the the port fails power-on diagnostic tests.

ciscoEsPortMdiMdix.name: ciscoEsPortMdiMdix
ciscoEsPortMdiMdix.description: Indicates whether the port is configured as MDI or MDIX or none (meaning not applicable). This object is also used to show the termination status for 10Base2 type ports.

ciscoEsPortHashOverflows.name: ciscoEsPortHashOverflows
ciscoEsPortHashOverflows.description: Number of times a hash bucket was full when trying to add an entry to the port address table.

ciscoEsPortTableOverflows.name: ciscoEsPortTableOverflows
ciscoEsPortTableOverflows.description: Number of times the address table was full when trying to add an entry to the port address table.

ciscoEsPortAddrAgingTime.name: ciscoEsPortAddrAgingTime
ciscoEsPortAddrAgingTime.description: Port level address aging time in minutes. Setting this object to zero disables address aging.

ciscoEsPortDemandAgingLevel.name: ciscoEsPortDemandAgingLevel
ciscoEsPortDemandAgingLevel.description: Threshold to demand age the port address table. All numbers refer to percentage of the address table. The only values accepted by the agent are 50,60,70,80,90 and 0. Setting the value to 0 disables demand aging.

ciscoEsPortCfgMode.name: ciscoEsPortCfgMode
ciscoEsPortCfgMode.description: Set bridging mode for the port.

ciscoEsPortActiveMode.name: ciscoEsPortActiveMode
ciscoEsPortActiveMode.description: Operational bridging mode for the port.

ciscoEsPortErrThreshold.name: ciscoEsPortErrThreshold
ciscoEsPortErrThreshold.description: Threshold error rate when the port moves from cut-through to store and forward mode.

ciscoEsPortLearningState.name: ciscoEsPortLearningState
ciscoEsPortLearningState.description: Configure learning state on this port.

ciscoEsPortRuntlessMode.name: ciscoEsPortRuntlessMode
ciscoEsPortRuntlessMode.description: Turn on/off runtless filtering on this port. When this this mode is turned on, no runts will be forwarded.

ciscoEsPortCDPTimeToLive.name: ciscoEsPortCDPTimeToLive
ciscoEsPortCDPTimeToLive.description: The advertised time-to-live parameter on all CDP messages generated by this switch on this vlan.

ciscoEsPortFastPort.name: ciscoEsPortFastPort
ciscoEsPortFastPort.description: Indicates whether the port is enable or disable for fast port support. When fast port is enable, port state will go to forwarding as soon as the link is up.

ciscoEsPortISLOperStatus.name: ciscoEsPortISLOperStatus
ciscoEsPortISLOperStatus.description: The current operational mode for an ISL port.

ciscoEsPortISLAdminStatus.name: ciscoEsPortISLAdminStatus
ciscoEsPortISLAdminStatus.description: Used to configure the DISL modes for an ISL trunk port.

ciscoEsPortStnEntry.name: ciscoEsPortStnEntry
ciscoEsPortStnEntry.description: Definition of the Conceptual row in the Port station table.

ciscoEsPortStnSwitchNumber.name: ciscoEsPortStnSwitchNumber
ciscoEsPortStnSwitchNumber.description: Switch number determined by the port number that the switch is connected to in a Matrix or as determined by the Stack Management software when two switches are connected back to back.

ciscoEsPortStnPortNum.name: ciscoEsPortStnPortNum
ciscoEsPortStnPortNum.description: Port number corresponding to this entry.

ciscoEsPortStnSrcFrames.name: ciscoEsPortStnSrcFrames
ciscoEsPortStnSrcFrames.description: Number of frames with this station as the source.

ciscoEsPortStnSrcBytes.name: ciscoEsPortStnSrcBytes
ciscoEsPortStnSrcBytes.description: Number of Bytes with this station as the source.

ciscoEsPortStnDestnFrames.name: ciscoEsPortStnDestnFrames
ciscoEsPortStnDestnFrames.description: Number of frames with this station as the destination.

ciscoEsPortStnDestnBytes.name: ciscoEsPortStnDestnBytes
ciscoEsPortStnDestnBytes.description: Number of bytes with this station as the destination.

ciscoEsPortStnPortOfExit.name: ciscoEsPortStnPortOfExit
ciscoEsPortStnPortOfExit.description: A bit string that identifies the ports that frames destined to this address are forwarded to when received on this port. Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the EtherSwitch is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'.

ciscoEsOptPortStaTable.name: ciscoEsOptPortStaTable
ciscoEsOptPortStaTable.description: A table of station addresses known at an individual port. This table is designed to reduce the number of SNMP GETNEXT requests. This is done by packing many values into an octet string. (The maximum size frame should be used to return the result.) The instance returned for a GETNEXT is the value that identifies the last 'row' in the octet string. When the table is completely retrieved with one or more GETNEXTs, duplicate entries may be present, and entries may be skipped if the table is changing while being retrieved.

ciscoEsOptPortStaEntry.name: ciscoEsOptPortStaEntry
ciscoEsOptPortStaEntry.description: Definition of the rows in the optimized port station address table. Rows can not be created or deleted via SNMP requests.

ciscoEsOptPortStaPos.name: ciscoEsOptPortStaPos
ciscoEsOptPortStaPos.description: Third index for items in the optimized port station address table.

ciscoEsOptPortStaVal.name: ciscoEsOptPortStaVal
ciscoEsOptPortStaVal.description: An OCTET STRING containing a multiple number of stations from a port station address table. Each entry is encoded in the following format: Station MAC address - 6 octets Location 1 - local 2 - remote - 1 octet Port of exit Mask - 4 octets Source Frame Count - 4 octets (integer in little endian) Destn Frame Count - 4 octets (integer in little endian) Source Byte Count - 4 octets (integer in little endian) Destn Byte Count - 4 octets (integer in little endian) The Port of exit mask is encoded in its raw form as stored in the switch. Octet 1 Bit position 7 6 5 4 3 2 1 0 Port Number 31 30 29 28 27 26 25 24 Octet 2 Bit position 7 6 5 4 3 2 1 0 Port Number 23 22 21 20 19 18 17 16 Octet 3 Bit position 7 6 5 4 3 2 1 0 Port Number 15 14 13 12 11 10 9 8 Octet 4 Bit position 7 6 5 4 3 2 1 0 Port Number 7 6 5 4 3 2 1 CPU

ciscoEsVLANPortEntry.name: ciscoEsVLANPortEntry
ciscoEsVLANPortEntry.description: Definition of each row in the vlan Table

ciscoEsVLANPortSwitchNumber.name: ciscoEsVLANPortSwitchNumber
ciscoEsVLANPortSwitchNumber.description: Switch number determined by the port number that the switch is connected to in a Matrix or as determined by the Stack Management software when two switches are connected back to back.

ciscoEsVLANPortPorts.name: ciscoEsVLANPortPorts
ciscoEsVLANPortPorts.description: The set of ports in this switch which belong to this VLAN. Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the EtherSwitch is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'.

ciscoEsVLANInfoEntry.name: ciscoEsVLANInfoEntry
ciscoEsVLANInfoEntry.description: Definition of each row in the vlan Table

ciscoEsVLANInfoState.name: ciscoEsVLANInfoState
ciscoEsVLANInfoState.description: Current state of the vlan. If a vlan has at least one port, it is considered active (1).

ciscoEsVLANInfoName.name: ciscoEsVLANInfoName
ciscoEsVLANInfoName.description: User defined name of the vlan.

ciscoEsVLANInfoBaseAddr.name: ciscoEsVLANInfoBaseAddr
ciscoEsVLANInfoBaseAddr.description: The MAC address assigned to this vlan. This address is the MAC address of the lowest numbered port in the vlan.

ciscoEsVLANInfoIfIndex.name: ciscoEsVLANInfoIfIndex
ciscoEsVLANInfoIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the interface entry corresponding to each vlan.

ciscoEsVLANInfoIpAddress.name: ciscoEsVLANInfoIpAddress
ciscoEsVLANInfoIpAddress.description: IP Address assigned to this vlan. Changes to the IP Address of the vlan to which the management station belongs cause loss of connectivity until the management station updates its information about the IP Address.

ciscoEsVLANInfoIpSubnetMask.name: ciscoEsVLANInfoIpSubnetMask
ciscoEsVLANInfoIpSubnetMask.description: The subnet mask for this vlan.

ciscoEsVLANInfoIpDefaultGateway.name: ciscoEsVLANInfoIpDefaultGateway
ciscoEsVLANInfoIpDefaultGateway.description: The IP Address of the default gateway for this VLAN.

ciscoEsVLANInfoStp.name: ciscoEsVLANInfoStp
ciscoEsVLANInfoStp.description: Turn Spanning tree on or off.

ciscoEsVLANInfoNumStations.name: ciscoEsVLANInfoNumStations
ciscoEsVLANInfoNumStations.description: Number of local stations (nodes) in the vlan.

ciscoEsVLANInfoMaxStations.name: ciscoEsVLANInfoMaxStations
ciscoEsVLANInfoMaxStations.description: Aggregate of the highest number of local stations (nodes) in the vlan calculated separately on each box.

ciscoEsVLANStpTable.name: ciscoEsVLANStpTable
ciscoEsVLANStpTable.description: Spanning tree information table for each vlan.

ciscoEsVLANStpEntry.name: ciscoEsVLANStpEntry
ciscoEsVLANStpEntry.description: Definition of each row in the vlan specific spanning tree information table.

ciscoEsVLANStpVLANIndex.name: ciscoEsVLANStpVLANIndex
ciscoEsVLANStpVLANIndex.description: Integer reference to the vlan number in the vlan table.

ciscoEsVLANStpPriority.name: ciscoEsVLANStpPriority
ciscoEsVLANStpPriority.description: The value of the write-able portion of the Bridge ID, i.e., the first two octets of the (8 octet long) Bridge ID. The other (last) 6 octets of the Bridge ID are given by the value of ciscoEsVLANBaseBridgeAddress. The bridge ID corresponds to the particular instance of spanning tree running in this vlan

ciscoEsVLANStpTimeSinceTopologyChange.name: ciscoEsVLANStpTimeSinceTopologyChange
ciscoEsVLANStpTimeSinceTopologyChange.description: The time (in hundredths of a second) since the last time a topology change was detected by the bridge entity.

ciscoEsVLANStpTopChanges.name: ciscoEsVLANStpTopChanges
ciscoEsVLANStpTopChanges.description: The total number of topology changes detected by this vlan since the management entity was last reset or initialized.

ciscoEsVLANStpDesignatedRoot.name: ciscoEsVLANStpDesignatedRoot
ciscoEsVLANStpDesignatedRoot.description: The bridge identifier of the root of the spanning tree as determined by the Spanning Tree Protocol as executed by this node. This value is used as the Root Identifier parameter in all Configuration Bridge PDUs originated by this vlan.

ciscoEsVLANStpRootCost.name: ciscoEsVLANStpRootCost
ciscoEsVLANStpRootCost.description: The cost of the path to the root as seen from this vlan.

ciscoEsVLANStpRootPort.name: ciscoEsVLANStpRootPort
ciscoEsVLANStpRootPort.description: The port number of the port which offers the lowest cost path from this vlan to the root bridge.

ciscoEsVLANStpMaxAge.name: ciscoEsVLANStpMaxAge
ciscoEsVLANStpMaxAge.description: The maximum age of Spanning Tree Protocol information learned from the network on any port before it is discarded, in units of hundredths of a second. This is the actual value that this vlan is currently using.

ciscoEsVLANStpHelloTime.name: ciscoEsVLANStpHelloTime
ciscoEsVLANStpHelloTime.description: The amount of time between the transmission of Configuration bridge PDUs by this node on any port when it is the root of the spanning tree or trying to become so, in units of hundredths of a second. This is the actual value that this vlan is currently using.

ciscoEsVLANStpHoldTime.name: ciscoEsVLANStpHoldTime
ciscoEsVLANStpHoldTime.description: This time value determines the interval length during which no more than two Configuration bridge PDUs shall be transmitted by this vlan, in units of hundredths of a second.

ciscoEsVLANStpForwardDelay.name: ciscoEsVLANStpForwardDelay
ciscoEsVLANStpForwardDelay.description: This time value, measured in units of hundredths of a second, controls how fast a port changes its spanning state when moving towards the Forwarding state. The value determines how long the port stays in each of the Listening and Learning states, which precede the Forwarding state. This value is also used, when a topology change has been detected and is underway, to age all dynamic entries in the Forwarding Database. [Note that this value is the one that this vlan is currently using, in contrast to ciscoEsVLANStpBridgeForwardDelay which is the value that this vlan and all others would start using if/when this vlan were to become the root.]

ciscoEsVLANStpBridgeMaxAge.name: ciscoEsVLANStpBridgeMaxAge
ciscoEsVLANStpBridgeMaxAge.description: The value that all bridges use for MaxAge when this vlan is acting as the root. Note that 802.1D-1990 specifies that the range for this parameter is related to the value of ciscoEsVLANStpBridgeHelloTime. The granularity of this timer is specified by 802.1D-1990 to be 1 second. An agent may return a badValue error if a set is attempted to a value which is not a whole number of seconds.

ciscoEsVLANStpBridgeHelloTime.name: ciscoEsVLANStpBridgeHelloTime
ciscoEsVLANStpBridgeHelloTime.description: The value that all bridges use for HelloTime when this vlan is acting as the root. The granularity of this timer is specified by 802.1D- 1990 to be 1 second. An agent may return a badValue error if a set is attempted to a value which is not a whole number of seconds.

ciscoEsVLANStpBridgeForwardDelay.name: ciscoEsVLANStpBridgeForwardDelay
ciscoEsVLANStpBridgeForwardDelay.description: The value that all bridges use for ForwardDelay when this vlan is acting as the root. Note that 802.1D-1990 specifies that the range for this parameter is related to the value of ciscoEsVLANStpBridgeMaxAge. The granularity of this timer is specified by 802.1D-1990 to be 1 second. An agent may return a badValue error if a set is attempted to a value which is not a whole number of seconds.

ciscoEsVLANStationEntry.name: ciscoEsVLANStationEntry
ciscoEsVLANStationEntry.description: Definition of each row in the vlan specific station table.

ciscoEsVLANStationVLANIndex.name: ciscoEsVLANStationVLANIndex
ciscoEsVLANStationVLANIndex.description: Integer reference to the vlan number in the vlan table.

ciscoEsVLANStationBoxNum.name: ciscoEsVLANStationBoxNum
ciscoEsVLANStationBoxNum.description: Integer reference to the switch number on which the table entry resides.

ciscoEsVLANStationPort.name: ciscoEsVLANStationPort
ciscoEsVLANStationPort.description: The source port for the Station.

ciscoEsVLANStationTraffic.name: ciscoEsVLANStationTraffic
ciscoEsVLANStationTraffic.description: A bit string that identifies with value of one of the ports that this station has generated traffic to or from. Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the EtherSwitch is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'.

ciscoEsOptVLANStaTable.name: ciscoEsOptVLANStaTable
ciscoEsOptVLANStaTable.description: A table of station addresses known at an individual port. This table is designed to reduce the number of SNMP GETNEXT requests. This is done by packing many values into an octet string. (The maximum size frame should be used to return the result.) The instance returned for a GETNEXT is the value that identifies the last 'row' in the octet string. When the table is completely retrieved with one or more GETNEXTs, duplicate entries may be present, and entries may be skipped if the table is changing while being retrieved.

ciscoEsOptVLANStaEntry.name: ciscoEsOptVLANStaEntry
ciscoEsOptVLANStaEntry.description: Definition of the rows in the optimized port station address table. Rows can not be created or deleted via SNMP requests.

ciscoEsOptVLANStaPos.name: ciscoEsOptVLANStaPos
ciscoEsOptVLANStaPos.description: Third index for items in the optimized port station address table.

ciscoEsOptVLANStaVal.name: ciscoEsOptVLANStaVal
ciscoEsOptVLANStaVal.description: An OCTET STRING containing a multiple number of stations from the vlan station address table. Each entry is encoded in the following format: Station MAC address - 6 octets Port of Entry - 1 octet Traffic Mask - 4 octets The traffic mask is encoded in its raw form as stored in the switch. Octet 1 Bit position 7 6 5 4 3 2 1 0 Port Number 31 30 29 28 27 26 25 24 Octet 2 Bit position 7 6 5 4 3 2 1 0 Port Number 23 22 21 20 19 18 17 16 Octet 3 Bit position 7 6 5 4 3 2 1 0 Port Number 15 14 13 12 11 10 9 8 Octet 4 Bit position 7 6 5 4 3 2 1 0 Port Number 7 6 5 4 3 2 1 CPU

ciscoEsTransitedConfiguredVLANs.name: ciscoEsTransitedConfiguredVLANs
ciscoEsTransitedConfiguredVLANs.description: A string of octets containing one bit per VLAN in the management domain. The first octet corresponds to VLANs with VlanIndex 1 through 8; the second octet to VLANs 9 through 16; etc. The most significant bit of each octet corresponds to the lowest value VlanIndex in that octet. If the bit correspond to a VLAN is set to '1', then the VLAN is a configured transited VLAN on the local device. (Default VLANs which must transit the local device are always considered to be 'configured transited VLANs'.) Any attempt to set a bit string which has: more bits set than the local device can transit; or does not have all bits set corresponding to default VLANs which must transit the device; or set any bits corresponding to non-existant VLANs (VLANs whose IDs are not defined in the management domain) will be completely rejected as an illegal value.

ciscoEsTransitedVLANs.name: ciscoEsTransitedVLANs
ciscoEsTransitedVLANs.description: A string of octets containing one bit per VLAN in the management domain. The first octet corresponds to VLANs with VlanIndex 1 through 8; the second octet to VLANs 9 through 16; etc. The most significant bit of each octet corresponds to the lowest value VlanIndex in that octet. If the bit corresponding to a VLAN is set to '1', then the VLAN transits the local device either because it was configured to or because it was selected to automatically by the selection algorithm.

ciscoEsECEntry.name: ciscoEsECEntry
ciscoEsECEntry.description: Definition of each row in the EtherChannel table.

ciscoEsECSwitchNumber.name: ciscoEsECSwitchNumber
ciscoEsECSwitchNumber.description: Switch number determined by the port number that the switch is connected to in a Matrix or as determined by the Stack Management software when two switches are connected back to back.

ciscoEsECNumber.name: ciscoEsECNumber
ciscoEsECNumber.description: The EtherChannel number for this row.

ciscoEsECPorts.name: ciscoEsECPorts
ciscoEsECPorts.description: The set of ports in this switch which are active in this EtherChannel. Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the EtherSwitch is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'.

ciscoEsFilterTable.name: ciscoEsFilterTable
ciscoEsFilterTable.description: Filters set up in the switch.

ciscoEsFilterEntry.name: ciscoEsFilterEntry
ciscoEsFilterEntry.description: Definition of each row in the filter table.

ciscoEsFilterSwitchNumber.name: ciscoEsFilterSwitchNumber
ciscoEsFilterSwitchNumber.description: Switch number determined by the port number that the switch is connected to in a Matrix or as determined by the Stack Management software when two switches are connected back to back.

ciscoEsFilterStationAddress.name: ciscoEsFilterStationAddress
ciscoEsFilterStationAddress.description: The destination MAC address in a frame to which this entry's filtering information applies.

ciscoEsFilterType.name: ciscoEsFilterType
ciscoEsFilterType.description: There are two types of filters (i) source filters which act on the source address portion of a packet and (ii) destination filters which act on the destination address portion of a packet.

ciscoEsFilterPorts.name: ciscoEsFilterPorts
ciscoEsFilterPorts.description: The set of ports to which this filter is applied. Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the EtherSwitch is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'.

ciscoEsFilterMask.name: ciscoEsFilterMask
ciscoEsFilterMask.description: The filter mask for this station. The semantics of the filter mask depend on the type of filter. Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the EtherSwitch is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'.

ciscoEsFilterRemoteSwitch.name: ciscoEsFilterRemoteSwitch
ciscoEsFilterRemoteSwitch.description: In case of destination filters you can specify a particular port in a remote box as the destination port for a given station address. A value of 0 indicates no remote switch is configured.

ciscoEsFilterRemotePort.name: ciscoEsFilterRemotePort
ciscoEsFilterRemotePort.description: In case of destination filters you can specify a particular port in a remote box as the destination port for a given station address. A value of 0 indicates no remote ports assigned.

ciscoEsFilterStatus.name: ciscoEsFilterStatus
ciscoEsFilterStatus.description: GET request always returns valid (1). Set this object to invalid (2) to delete an entry.

ciscoEsRouterEntry.name: ciscoEsRouterEntry
ciscoEsRouterEntry.description: Definition of each row in the Router Table

ciscoEsRouterBox.name: ciscoEsRouterBox
ciscoEsRouterBox.description: Index into the router table row.

ciscoEsRouterPort.name: ciscoEsRouterPort
ciscoEsRouterPort.description: Index into the router table column.

ciscoEsRouterOpState.name: ciscoEsRouterOpState
ciscoEsRouterOpState.description: GET request returns up (1) down(2) for operation state.

ciscoEsRouterNetAddr.name: ciscoEsRouterNetAddr
ciscoEsRouterNetAddr.description: The IP address of the router.

ciscoEsRouterBoardId.name: ciscoEsRouterBoardId
ciscoEsRouterBoardId.description: The Board Id of the router.

ciscoEsRouterRev.name: ciscoEsRouterRev
ciscoEsRouterRev.description: The Board Rev of the router.

ciscoEsStackCfgChange.name: ciscoEsStackCfgChange
ciscoEsStackCfgChange.description: This trap is generated when there is a change in the stack configuration i.e. when either a new switch is added to the stack or a switch leaves a stack. ciscoEsNumSwitches indicates the current number of switches which are part of the stack. The management station has to update its stack information according to the stack table.

ciscoEsStackProStackMatrixChange.name: ciscoEsStackProStackMatrixChange
ciscoEsStackProStackMatrixChange.description: This trap is generated when the stack switches over from primary to secondary Matrix or from secondary back to primary Matrix.

ciscoEsStackTempChange.name: ciscoEsStackTempChange
ciscoEsStackTempChange.description: This trap is generated when the temperature in a switch exceeds normal or returns to normal.

ciscoEsPortStrNFwdEntry.name: ciscoEsPortStrNFwdEntry
ciscoEsPortStrNFwdEntry.description: This trap is generated when a port automatically enters store and forward mode when the error rate exceeds the threshold.

ciscoEsVLANNewRoot.name: ciscoEsVLANNewRoot
ciscoEsVLANNewRoot.description: This trap is a vlan specific version of the newRoot trap as described in RFC1493. The newRoot trap indicates that the sending agent has become the new root of the Spanning Tree; the trap is sent by a bridge soon after its election as the new root, e.g., upon expiration of the Topology Change Timer immediately subsequent to its election. Implementation of this trap is optional.

ciscoEsVLANTopologyChange.name: ciscoEsVLANTopologyChange
ciscoEsVLANTopologyChange.description: This trap is a vlan specific version of the topologyChange trap as described in RFC1493. A topologyChange trap is sent by a bridge when any of its configured ports transitions from the Learning state to the Forwarding state, or from the Forwarding state to the Blocking state. The trap is not sent if a newRoot trap is sent for the same transition. Implementation of this trap is optional.

ciscoEsEtherChannelFailed.name: ciscoEsEtherChannelFailed
ciscoEsEtherChannelFailed.description: This trap is sent when one of the links in an EtherChannel fail. The variable ciscoEsECPorts contains the ports which are operational in the EtherChannel.
